            <Text fill="WHITE" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="So lets say you want to send some pictures to a friend, it’s easier to send them in a single .tar rather than 3 separate downloads. Use the tar command, the appropriate flags, then the name of what you want the archive to be called. Leave spaces between that, then each file you want to add.&#10;&#10;tar -cvf holidaysnaps.tar holidayphoto1 holidayphoto2 holiday photo3&#10;&#10;The flags used:&#10;&#10;c – Create, this is because you want to create a new archive&#10;v -  Vervose, this tell the program to be verbose and let us see what it's doing&#10;f -  Filename, this means you can create a filename for your .tar file.&#10;&#10;To extract the contents of a tar file, use:&#10;&#10; tar -xvf myholidaysnaps.tar&#10;&#10;x – Extract&#10;v – Verbose, this tell the program to be verbose and let us see what it's doing&#10;f -  Filename, tells tar that the next parameter is the file name of the archive" wrappingWidth="456.0">
